reviews.headline: Multi-use must have
reviews.comments: I will never not have some of this stocked in my makeup bag. It's great as a light powder foundation, it helps mattify shiny trouble spots, and my favorite thing is that it can be used to blend out spots with unwanted eyeshadow application. It basically works like an eyeshadow eraser and that has made doing my eye makeup so much less stressful.

I can use this lightly just on my under eyes but it truly isn't my favorite. It has great coverage though! I just wish i could make it work better

Not a whole lot of coverage & made me break out. Definitely going back to Clinique sheer matte pressed powder! And I use other Maybelline products which I love! Sorry Maybelline, this one didn't cut it for me üòî

reviews.headline: Matte for days
reviews.comments: Ok so I heard this is a dupe for a very popular powder and I own the other one, so let's compare. Buildable, yes. Go light and powdering, or pack it on. Very good coverage and you don't need a ton to even out your skin tone and give your skin a much better texture. Slightly minimizes pores. A lot better if you add a primer. This is a true matte powder. Almost a little too matte for me. I find that if I build a couple layers it just feels heavy and I don't like that so I'll stick to setting my makeup lightly. All in all, great dupe for the price point

faceoff_positive.comments:
I recently moved to NC and it's hot and humid all the time. I have very oily skin (the entire face not just the T zone). Anyone who lives down south knows that foundation is a challenge because it melts off your face in the heat. I did some research and powder is the way to go for oily skin, do not go with liquid foundation. 

I'm naturally tan so I bought the 220 (natural Beige) shade. I originally bought the liquid foundation but returned it because after 8 hours outside my face was a shiny disaster. I put the powder to the test: I went outside and did manual labor and sweat my butt off, I couldn't believe how well it controlled the oil and shine, my savior!!! Even if you have normal or combination skin still consider powder in the summer time trust me. 

The shade matched my skin tone to perfection it disappears and provides light to medium coverage. It looks more natural than liquid because it doesn't cover your actual skin but blends in and covers redness. I had multiple people say they couldn't tell I was wearing makeup. It's great for oily skin and if you have large pores it covers that up to. 

I also highly recommend buying a moisturizer with spf designed just for oily skin, don't use liquid foundation on top of your moisturizer just use the powder and you'll see a big difference in terms of oil and shine control. Wow I'm sold and hooked!
faceoff_positive.headline: A MUST for oily skin in hot and humid climate.

faceoff_negative.comments: The one redeeming factor about this powder is the Porcelain color is a perfect match for fair skin that has yellow undertones. Other than that, I tried this powder a few times with the matching foundation, and hated it every time. Now, my skin tends to be drier during winter and this stuff is supposed to be for normal to oily skin. So it could be that it just wasn't the right formula for my skin type. But either way, the coverage was not good, both foundation and powder clung to every little dry spot no matter how moisturized my skin was, and my face was far from matte and poreless. I do not recommend this product to anyone who has even the slightest bit of dryness to their skin, nor to someone who likes good coverage.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not for me
